1. lazy-brush (brush stabilization / drawing smoothing)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Component name:  lazy-brush
  Author:           Jan Hug (GitHub: dulnan)
  Repository:      https://github.com/dulnan/lazy-brush
  Package (npm):   https://www.npmjs.com/package/lazy-brush
  License:         MIT License
  Version used:    2.0.2

  File included in this plugin:
    mod/pdfannotator/lib/lazy-brush/lazy-brush.umd.cjs

  Source of the file (unchanged, official UMD build from the package):
    https://unpkg.com/lazy-brush@2.0.2/lib/lazy-brush.umd.cjs

  Purpose:
    Smooth drawing with mouse, finger or other pointing device (brush
    stabilization). It is used in the Drawing tool to reduce hand tremor
    and produce smoother strokes. The library is loaded in locallib.php
    and integrated in js_new/pdfannotator_new.js (and versioned copies).

  What was taken:
    Only the single file lazy-brush.umd.cjs from the above URL. No other
    files or code snippets from the lazy-brush repository were copied.
    The integration code in pdfannotator_new.js (calls to LazyBrush
    constructor, update(), getBrushCoordinates()) was written for this
    project and is not from the lazy-brush repo.

